@startuml
' Rendered automatically by GitHub Actions
title IAB Tech Lab Agentic Advertising - Architecture (Control vs Data Plane)
left to right direction
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 12
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

rectangle "CONTROL PLANE (execution)" as CP #E8F4FF {
  [Agentic Direct\n(A2A + MCP + OpenDirect v2.1)] as AD
  [Buyer Agent\n(buy-side automation)] as BA
  [Seller Agent\n(supply-side automation)] as SA
}

rectangle "DATA PLANE (signals)" as DP #FFF3E6 {
  [Agentic Audiences / UCP\n(identity + context + reinforcement)\nembeddings / vectors] as UCP
}

BA --> AD : discover inventory\ncreate/update orders\n(OpenDirect ops via MCP/A2A)
AD --> SA : list/search products\nnegotiate/confirm\n(OpenDirect v2.1)
SA --> AD : Deal ID + confirmation
AD --> BA : Deal ID

BA --> UCP : create/share\nintent embedding
UCP --> SA : audience validation\n(vector similarity / policy)
SA --> UCP : reinforcement/response\n(outcomes, feedback)

note right of UCP
UCP/Agentic Audiences is the "signal fabric":
- identity
- context
- reinforcement
shared as embeddings to enable fast agent-to-agent decisions.
end note

note left of AD
Agentic Direct is the "execution fabric":
schema-driven tools from OpenAPI (OpenDirect),
exposed to agents via MCP + A2A routing/task mgmt.
end note
@enduml

